distinfo.techpreq: To use this data requires software that supports SDC files.

procstep.procdesc: The following steps were performed by ESRI: Extracted the National Parks from the National Park Service, the National Forests from ESRI ArcUSA 1:2M and the rest of the parks from Geographic Data Technology Dynamap/2000 v7.3. Converted to North American Datum of 1983 (NAD83). Created ArcGIS® layer file (.lyr). Created projection file (.prj). Ran ArcView GIS Avenue™ request ExportClean, and created spatial indices. Converted the data set to SDC.
The following steps were performed by ESRI: Added SQMI attribute and calculated its values.

horizpa.horizpar: The geospatial part of this data set was extracted from several sources at different scales. The positional accuracy is unknown.

dataqual.logic: No duplicate features are present. The shapefile is converted to SDC (Smart Data Compression) format in ArcSDE®. This verifies and validates the geometry.
dataqual.complete: After processing, the data set is checked for drawing display and number of records and file sizes compared with source materials.
